questions.question:
A Java developer is working with an `Object obj` and needs to check if it's an instance of `String`, and if so, perform an operation using the `String` reference. Before Java 16, they would write:
java
if (obj instanceof String) {
    String s = (String) obj;
    // ... use s
}

How can this code be concisely rewritten using a feature introduced in Java 16?

options:
java
if (obj instanceof String s && s != null) {
    // ... use s
}
java
if (obj.getClass() == String.class) {
    String s = (String) obj;
    // ... use s
}
java
if (obj instanceof String s) {
    // ... use s
}
java
String s = (String) obj;
if (s != null) {
    // ... use s
}

questions.answer:
java
if (obj instanceof String s) {
    // ... use s
}
